I’ve been thinking a lot about how we tend to focus on the big moments in life—graduations, new jobs, moving to a new place. But what really makes life beautiful are the small moments in between. The quiet mornings with a cup of coffee, the laughter shared with friends, the moments of peace when you’re alone. It’s easy to overlook those little things, but they’re the ones that truly shape our experiences. So here’s to the simple joys we sometimes take for granted.